<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="259" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1369,1792]" pageId="1" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1369,1395]" pageId="1" pageNumber="259">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The genus is characterized by the presence of a small bulb; embolus with or without an obvious bifurcation in the middle. Carapace of males with obvious wrinkles, no apophysis in known species, cephalic part of carapace clearly the highest. Metatarsi are ca. 2–3 times longer than tarsi (modified from 
<bibRefCitation author="Wunderlich, J." box="[1164,1361,1441,1467]" pageId="1" pageNumber="259" pagination="524 - 675" refId="ref5915" refString="Wunderlich, J. (2008) The dominance of ancient spider families of the Araneae: Haplogyne in the Cretaceous, and the late diversification of advanced ecribellate spiders of the Entelegynae after the Cretaceous-Tertiary boundary extinction events, with descriptions of new families. In: Wunderlich, J. (Ed.), Beitrage zur Araneologie, 5, pp. 524 - 675." type="journal article" year="2008">Wunderlich 2008</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Wunderlich, J." box="[1373,1432,1441,1468]" pageId="1" pageNumber="259" pagination="21 - 408" refId="ref5984" refString="Wunderlich, J. (2015) On the evolution and the classification of spiders, the Mesozoic spider faunas, and descriptions of new Cretaceous taxa mainly in amber from Myanmar (Burma) (Arachnida: Araneae). In: Wunderlich, J. (Ed.), Beitrage zur Araneologie, 9, pp. 21 - 408." type="journal article" year="2015">2015</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Wunderlich, J." box="[151,212,1477,1503]" pageId="1" pageNumber="259" pagination="72 - 279" refId="ref6048" refString="Wunderlich, J. (2017) New and rare fossil spiders (Araneae) in mid Cretaceous amber from Myanmar (Burma), including the description of new extinct families of the suborders Mesothelae and Opisthothelae as well as notes on the taxonomy, the evolution and the biogeography of the Mesothelae. In: Wunderlich, J. (Ed.), Beitrage zur Araneologie, 10, pp. 72 - 279." type="journal article" year="2017">2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="259" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1369,1792]" pageId="1" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1513,1539]" pageId="1" pageNumber="259">Remarks.</emphasis>
† 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2008" box="[336,483,1513,1539]" class="Arachnida" family="Eopsilodercidae" genus="Furcembolus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[336,483,1513,1539]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="259">Furcembolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was established by Wunderlich in 2008, placed in the fossil family † 
<taxonomicName authority="Wunderlich, 2008" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2008" class="Arachnida" family="Eopsilodercidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Eopsilodercidae 
<bibRefCitation author="Wunderlich, J." box="[151,358,1549,1575]" pageId="1" pageNumber="259" pagination="524 - 675" refId="ref5915" refString="Wunderlich, J. (2008) The dominance of ancient spider families of the Araneae: Haplogyne in the Cretaceous, and the late diversification of advanced ecribellate spiders of the Entelegynae after the Cretaceous-Tertiary boundary extinction events, with descriptions of new families. In: Wunderlich, J. (Ed.), Beitrage zur Araneologie, 5, pp. 524 - 675." type="journal article" year="2008">Wunderlich, 2008</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but Wunderlich wasn’t sure about their relationships. † 
<emphasis box="[1001,1171,1549,1575]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="259">Praeterpaculla</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wunderlich, J." box="[1180,1383,1549,1576]" pageId="1" pageNumber="259" pagination="21 - 408" refId="ref5984" refString="Wunderlich, J. (2015) On the evolution and the classification of spiders, the Mesozoic spider faunas, and descriptions of new Cretaceous taxa mainly in amber from Myanmar (Burma) (Arachnida: Araneae). In: Wunderlich, J. (Ed.), Beitrage zur Araneologie, 9, pp. 21 - 408." type="journal article" year="2015">Wunderlich, 2015</bibRefCitation>
was erected by Wunderlich under the family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pickard-Cambridge" authorityYear="1873" box="[609,791,1585,1611]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetrablemmidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Tetrablemmidae</taxonomicName>
with five new species. After studying further specimens, the genus † 
<emphasis box="[283,453,1621,1647]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="259">Praeterpaculla</emphasis>
was regarded as a junior synonym of † 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2008" box="[908,1055,1621,1647]" class="Arachnida" family="Eopsilodercidae" genus="Furcembolus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[908,1055,1621,1647]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="259">Furcembolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and † 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2008" box="[1134,1281,1621,1647]" class="Arachnida" family="Eopsilodercidae" genus="Furcembolus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1134,1281,1621,1647]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="259">Furcembolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
turned out to be a taxon of Pacullinae, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wunderlich 2017)" baseAuthorityName="Wunderlich" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[443,851,1657,1683]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetrablemmidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Tetrablemmidae (
<bibRefCitation author="Wunderlich, J." box="[640,843,1657,1683]" pageId="1" pageNumber="259" pagination="72 - 279" refId="ref6048" refString="Wunderlich, J. (2017) New and rare fossil spiders (Araneae) in mid Cretaceous amber from Myanmar (Burma), including the description of new extinct families of the suborders Mesothelae and Opisthothelae as well as notes on the taxonomy, the evolution and the biogeography of the Mesothelae. In: Wunderlich, J. (Ed.), Beitrage zur Araneologie, 10, pp. 72 - 279." type="journal article" year="2017">Wunderlich 2017</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. After the restoration of family status of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wheeler et al. 2017)" baseAuthorityName="Wheeler" baseAuthorityYear="2017" class="Arachnida" family="Pacullidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Pacullidae (
<bibRefCitation author="Wheeler, W. C. &amp; Coddington, J. A. &amp; Crowley, L. M. &amp; Dimitrov, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A. &amp; Griswold, C. E. &amp; Hormiga, G. &amp; Prendini, L &amp; Ramirez, M. J. &amp; Sierwald, P. &amp; Almeida-Silva, L. M. &amp; Alvarez-Padilla, F. &amp; Arnedo, M. A. &amp; Benavides, L. R. &amp; Benjamin, S. P. &amp; Bond, J. E. &amp; Grismado, C. J. &amp; Hasan, E. &amp; Hedin, M. &amp; Izquierdo, M. A. &amp; Labarque, F. M. &amp; Ledford, J. &amp; Lopardo, L. &amp; Maddison, W. P. &amp; Miller, J. A. &amp; Piacentini, L. N. &amp; Platnick, N. I. &amp; Polotow, D. &amp; Silva-Davila, D. &amp; Scharff, N. &amp; Szuts, T. &amp; Ubick, D. &amp; Vink, C. &amp; Wood, H. M. &amp; Zhang, J. X." box="[159,389,1693,1719]" pageId="1" pageNumber="259" pagination="576 - 616" refId="ref5613" refString="Wheeler, W. C., Coddington, J. A., Crowley, L. M., Dimitrov, D., Goloboff, P. A., Griswold, C. E., Hormiga, G., Prendini, L, Ramirez, M. J., Sierwald, P., Almeida-Silva, L. M., Alvarez-Padilla, F., Arnedo, M. A., Benavides, L. R., Benjamin, S. P., Bond, J. E., Grismado, C. J., Hasan, E., Hedin, M., Izquierdo, M. A., Labarque, F. M., Ledford, J., Lopardo, L., Maddison, W. P., Miller, J. A., Piacentini, L. N., Platnick, N. I., Polotow, D., Silva-Davila, D., Scharff, N., Szuts, T., Ubick, D., Vink, C., Wood, H. M. &amp; Zhang, J. X. (2017) The spider tree of life: phylogeny of Araneae based on target-gene analyses from an extensive taxon sampling. Cladistics, 33 (6), 576 - 616. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / cla. 12182" type="journal article" year="2017">
Wheeler 
<emphasis box="[264,321,1693,1719]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="259">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Magalhaes, I. L. F. &amp; Azevedo, G. H. F. &amp; Michalik, P. &amp; Ramirez, M. J." box="[410,680,1693,1719]" pageId="1" pageNumber="259" pagination="184 - 217" refId="ref4843" refString="Magalhaes, I. L. F., Azevedo, G. H. F., Michalik, P. &amp; Ramirez, M. J. (2020) The fossil record of spiders revisited: implications for calibrating trees and evidence for a major faunal turnover since the Mesozoic. Biological Reviews, 95 (1), 184 - 217. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / brv. 12559" type="journal article" year="2020">
Magalhaes 
<emphasis box="[540,597,1693,1719]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="259">et al.</emphasis>
(2020)
</bibRefCitation>
proposed that † 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2008" box="[864,1011,1693,1719]" class="Arachnida" family="Eopsilodercidae" genus="Furcembolus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[864,1011,1693,1719]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="259">Furcembolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be listed under 
<taxonomicName box="[1278,1398,1693,1719]" class="Arachnida" family="Pacullidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pacullidae</taxonomicName>
. At present, † 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2008" box="[260,407,1729,1755]" class="Arachnida" family="Eopsilodercidae" genus="Furcembolus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[260,407,1729,1755]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="259">Furcembolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only genus of extinct 
<taxonomicName box="[722,842,1729,1755]" class="Arachnida" family="Pacullidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pacullidae</taxonomicName>
, including nine known species and three new species described in this paper.
</paragraph>
